<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="771" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.48/74: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-30"><hi rend="italic">April 30,
                                1919</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your April 28, and April 29. Express appropriately to Salvadorean
                            Government deep sympathy and regret of Government and <pb facs="0887" n="802" xml:id="pg_802"/> people of United States on account of
                            earthquake and hope that loss of life may not be as great as reported.
                            American Red Cross advised of request for 100 tents.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>